cs.CL, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with the problem of synthesizing SQL queries from natural language, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and database systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel approach that involves a sketch-based approach, a sequence-to-set model, and a column attention mechanism, which are all related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. The paper also evaluates its approach on the WikiSQL task, which involves information retrieval and database systems, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases) possible categories as well.
